Recharging process complete.
Energy levels at maximum.
8:
A gentle morning breeze.
Today will be another beautiful day.
11: Justice... is the name of this flower.
15: And so, I have chosen to fight.
19: Understood. Let us hear more, then.
22:
In my home world, I belong to a
peacekeeping force known as the
Aegis Squadron.
23:
They function as protectors of law
and order in the land, though they
also served as an elite troop under
the Administrator's control and
supervision.
24:
Which is to say that we were directly
involved in the memory wiping
process.
28:
It is also highly probable that I
managed internal affairs and
oversaw purges of... undesirables.
31: It's probable—so you are not certain?
36:
There are gaps in my memory. It is
likely that I, too, was subjected to a
wipe.
43:
I have dreams.
Dreams whose importance I cannot
fathom, though they seem
significant.
49:
Surrender yourselves immediately.
The orders calling for your
elimination have already been
processed and approved.
51:
Sera… What about all those whose
memories were wiped? Will you not
protect them? What happened to
your sense of justice?
52:
Was I mistaken when I named that
flower after you...
57: That is why I must fight.
63:
Yes. It is imperative that we keep the
location of this town secret from the
Aegis Squadron.
65:
Only I can subdue them. I will
endeavor to keep the destruction to
a minimum.
67:
I need to be the one who puts an
end to this.
71:
I understand.
But only on one condition.
73:
Know that we won't sit idly by if you
should not return in time. We will
look for you and help you. Can you
agree with those terms?
78:
Yes! You have my gratitude,
Commander.
81:
That will be my final order as your
commanding officer. Consider me
retired.
93:
Spectacular! That's quite a display
you put on there.
97:
Rec Register… Tell me, if we
successfully breach the Aegis
Squadron's system, will we be able
to restore everyone's memory?
100:
Of course. We've got proof it's
possible: memories the
Administrator erased have already
been restored to many.
101:
It's likely the Aegis Squadron has its
own restricted domain, where they
store the extricated memories of
their own kind.
102:
If we can break through that firewall,
then perhaps Dia's song will reach
them and stir their memories.
109:
I'm afraid I can make no guarantee
for YOUR memories, however.
116:
The one who wiped your memories
was no member of the Aegis
Squadron. Nor was it the
Administrator herself.
117:
It was someone who knew all too
well the most simple way to put an
end to pain.
125:
It has been a while, Commander
Sera.
126:
But I'm afraid this is the end. No one
is to go beyond here.
130:
That blue flower… Do you remember
the name you gave to it?
135:
If you have forgotten, then I will
remind you.
137:
Of our crimes.
Of the precious moments we spent
together.
139: Of the candid words we shared.
151:
A gentle morning breeze.
Today will be another beautiful day.
